comment:
He isn‚Äôt exactly someone I have any interest in but why is it ok for a woman to use his DNA and bring a child into the world that he has clearly changed his mind about? 
If this had happened naturally then obviously that‚Äôs 100% a different situation and women should always have control over their own bodies & it would have been wrong for him to deny the child if she had decided to keep the baby. However this was embryos from a relationship that has long since finished & it takes sometimes years for women who have created embryos with their husbands or partners to be given permission to use them if, for example the man has sadly passed away, yet she has used these embryos & implanted to a surrogate after he has allegedly stated he no longer wants these eggs mixed with his DNA to be used.
That‚Äôs surely a level of manipulation that goes too far? Seems like a cash cow baby for her as if not she could have had her egg fertilised by a random sp3rm donor & still used a surrogate. 
The child deserves better than to grow up & maybe become aware that their biological father was against them being born or to be dragged through courts if he fights for access to see his daughter as she will use his redacted permission as a stick to beat him with stating he didn‚Äôt want this child so why should we share custody. Yet I‚Äôve a feeling she will still expect him to financially support the baby while denying him any form of relationship with the child which is so very wrong and just sad for the kid. 
Maybe she also is delusional to expect them to get back together to raise the baby as she seems to just be a manipulative horror story by her actions thus far. 

Wonder if the surrogate was hidden from everyone just incase he found out as with his money and power he could have made things very difficult & enforced a termination due to her not having the rights to use the embryos. 

I‚Äôm normally an advocate for it always being the woman‚Äôs choice over her body but she used another woman‚Äôs body & DNA from a man who she no longer was on speaking terms with & I just feel this makes the whole thing a bit icky. 
Nothing against this innocent child at all but this is totally messed up
